(617, 8, 'item_1_content', 'Mr. Gaché serves as the firm''s Managing Litigation Partner. Mr. Gaché came to the firm in February, 2011 after spending 23 years with the statewide law firm of Broad and Cassel. In his role as Managing Litigation Partner, Mr. Gaché is responsible for all aspects of the firm''s litigation practice. Mr. Gaché is a Florida Bar Board Certified Business Litigation attorney, and uses his experience to guide and direct the foreclosure, litigation and trial teams within the firm. He is also the firm''s point of contact for the Florida courts, in particular, the chief judges of the various circuits. In addition, Mr. Gaché oversees the firm''s compliance with its clients'' audit requirements, as well as the implementation of the firm''s overall practices and procedures.\r\n\r\nattorney, and uses his experience to guide and direct the foreclosure, litigation and trial teams within the firm. He is also the firm''s point of contact for the Florida courts, in particular, the chief judges of the various circuits. In addition, Mr. Gaché oversees the firm''s compliance with its clients'' audit requirements, as well as the implementation of the firm''s overall practices and procedures.\r\n\r\nMr. Gaché is AV® Rated by Martindale Hubbell and has consistently been listed as a "Florida Super Lawyer" by Law &amp; Politics magazine, "Top Attorney" in Commercial Litigation by the South Florida Legal Guide and a "Florida Legal Elite" attorney in Business Law and Litigation. He has served on several Florida Bar committees and currently serves on a select committee of business litigation attorneys chosen by the Florida Supreme Court which recently completed drafting Florida’s first Standard Jury Instructions for Business and Contract Cases.'),
