(681, 129, 'item_0_content', 'Shapiro, Fishman &amp; Gaché offers a full range of bankruptcy related legal services for our creditor clients.  Our attorneys are trained to represent lenders and other creditors in Chapter 7, 12 and 13 cases, as well as all associated adversary proceedings.  The firm’s bankruptcy services include a review of the initial petition and all accompanying schedules; a full review of any out-of-state bankruptcy cases to determine their effect on the pending Florida filing; appearance at Section 341 meetings; preparation of proofs of claim and defending objections thereto; preparation and argument of motions for relief and/or motions for adequate protection; drafting plan objections; review of chapter 11 disclosure statements; preparation of supplemental notice of payment changes; preparation of motions to value or determine secured status of liens; and bankruptcy appeals to the district court or directly to the 11th Circuit Court of Appeals in Atlanta.'),
